## Section 1 — Page Layout & Structure

### 1.1 Overall Page Layout

The Scenario Planner page uses a two-tab structure at the top — **Calculator** and **Scenario Planner** — consistent with the existing tab navigation already in place. The Scenario Planner tab is the focus of this spec.

The inputs layer occupies the full width of the page content area. It is not a sidebar, not a panel — it is the primary content of the page. Clean, focused, no competing elements.

**Vertical stack — top to bottom:**

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  PAGE HEADER                                        │
│  "Scenario Planner"                                 │
│  Subtitle: "Build and save growth scenarios         │
│  for comparison"                                    │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  BLOCK 1 — BASELINE CONFIGURATION                   │
│  Auto-populated from Agency Snapshot                │
│  Editable fields                                    │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  BLOCK 2 — SCENARIO TARGET CONFIGURATION            │
│  Preset chips (top)                                 │
│  Timeframe selector                                 │
│  Slider + value inputs for each target field        │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  BLOCK 3 — RUN & SAVE ACTIONS                       │
│  Run Scenario button                                │
│  Inline save prompt (appears after run)             │
│  Confirmation state (appears after save)            │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

**No output content appears in this layer.** No pressure cards, no charts, no metrics table. Those belong in the comparison section below (separate pass).

### 1.2 Page Width & Spacing

- Content area: max-width consistent with rest of platform
- Block padding: 24px internal padding on all blocks
- Block gap: 16px between blocks
- Field row gap: 16px between input rows within blocks

### 1.3 Visual Hierarchy Principle

The three blocks should feel like sequential steps — not three equal panels. The visual weight should guide the eye downward: configure baseline → set target → run and save. Subtle step numbering (1, 2, 3) or a light progress indicator reinforces this without being heavy-handed.

