## Section 2 — Component Specifications

### 2.1 Block 1 — Baseline Configuration

**Purpose:** Establish the starting point for all scenario calculations. Defaults to Agency Snapshot current state. Fully editable.

#### Header Row

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  ① BASELINE                          [⟳ Sync Snapshot] │
│  Your current agency state                          │
│  ● Using Agency Snapshot data                       │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

- Block label: "BASELINE" — small caps or uppercase, muted color, step number "①" prefix
- Subtitle: "Your current agency state" — light weight, small
- Source indicator: Small dot + "Using Agency Snapshot data" — muted green dot, small text
  - Changes to muted amber dot + "Custom baseline" if any field is edited
- Sync button: "⟳ Sync Snapshot" — text button, top right of block header. Re-pulls from snapshot and resets any edits. Subtle — not a primary action.

#### Field Layout

Two-column grid. Seven fields total — arrange as 3 rows of 2 plus 1 full-width at bottom, or 4 rows of 2 (one row has a single field centered or left-aligned).

Recommended arrangement:
```
[ Annual AGI ]          [ Gross Revenue ]
[ Profit Margin % ]     [ Client Count ]
[ ACV ]                 [ Retention Rate % ]
[ Team FTEs ]
```

#### Individual Field Component (Baseline)

Each baseline field is a standard labeled input — no slider needed here, these are the known current values.

```
┌────────────────────────────┐
│ Annual AGI                 │
│ $ [ 1,200,000            ] │
└────────────────────────────┘
```

- Label: small, muted, above the field
- Input: clean bordered input field, right-aligned numeric value
- Currency fields show $ prefix inside field
- Percentage fields show % suffix inside field
- On edit: field border highlights (platform accent color), source indicator updates to "Custom baseline"
- Validation: numeric only, no negative values

