### 2.2 Block 2 — Scenario Target Configuration

**Purpose:** Define the growth target for this scenario using presets, sliders, or direct value entry.

#### Header Row

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  ② SCENARIO TARGET                                  │
│  Define your growth scenario                        │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

#### Sub-section A — Quick Presets

Four preset chips arranged horizontally. Selecting one populates all target slider fields relative to baseline. Does not lock fields — all remain editable after selection.

```
[ Steady Climb ]  [ Active Growth ]  [ Aggressive Scale ]  [ Positioning Shift ]
```

**Preset definitions (relative to baseline):**

| Preset | AGI | Clients | ACV | Margin | Retention | FTEs | Timeframe |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| Steady Climb | +20% | +15% | +5% | hold | hold | +15% | 24mo |
| Active Growth | +40% | +25% | +10% | -2% | hold | +30% | 24mo |
| Aggressive Scale | +75% | +40% | +5% | -5% | -3% | +60% | 18mo |
| Positioning Shift | +30% | +5% | +25% | +3% | hold | +10% | 24mo |

**Chip visual states:**
- Default: outlined chip, muted border, light background
- Hover: slightly elevated, border darkens
- Selected: filled background (platform accent color), white text, checkmark prefix
- Selecting a different chip deselects the current one
- Editing any slider after preset selection deselects the preset chip (no preset is "active" once customized)

#### Sub-section B — Timeframe Selector

Sits between presets and the field inputs. Clean segmented control — not a dropdown.

```
TIMEFRAME
[ 12 Months ]  [ 24 Months ]  [ 36 Months ]
```

- Selected segment: filled, dark background or accent
- Default selection: 24 Months
- Changing timeframe recalculates all resolved absolute values on the sliders in real time

#### Sub-section C — Target Field Inputs

Seven fields — one per metric. Each field is a full-width row consisting of three connected elements: label, slider, and value display. Arranged vertically, one row per metric.

**Individual Target Field Row:**

```
Annual AGI (Target)
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
+30%  ●━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━  [ $1,560,000 ]
      ├── baseline: $1,200,000 ──────────────────────
```

**Component breakdown:**

**Percentage badge** (left of slider)
- Shows the relative change from baseline as a percentage
- Updates in real time as slider moves
- Color: green for positive change, amber for negative change (margin compression, retention drop)
- Format: +30% / -5% / 0%

**Slider**
- Full-width between the percentage badge and the value display
- Range: configurable per metric (see ranges below)
- Snap points: none — continuous
- Track: thin, rounded. Left of thumb: accent color. Right of thumb: muted gray.
- Thumb: small filled circle, slightly elevated on hover
- Baseline marker: a subtle tick mark on the slider track at the 0% position so the founder can always see where "no change" is

**Value display** (right of slider)
- Shows the resolved absolute value in real time
- Format matches the metric: currency ($1,560,000), percentage (28%), integer (16 clients)
- **Clickable** — clicking the value turns it into an editable input field
- In edit mode: input field with focus ring, cursor at end of value
- On blur or Enter: value locks, slider repositions to match, percentage badge updates
- Small edit icon (pencil, 12px) appears on hover before click to signal editability

**Baseline reference line**
- Below the slider: small muted text showing "baseline: [value]"
- Always visible — grounds the relative adjustment in the actual starting number

**Slider Range Defaults Per Metric:**

| Metric | Min | Max | Default |
|---|---|---|---|
| Annual AGI | -10% | +150% | +30% |
| Gross Revenue | -10% | +150% | +30% |
| Profit Margin | -15% | +15% | 0% |
| Client Count | -10% | +100% | +20% |
| ACV | -20% | +100% | +5% |
| Retention Rate | -20% | +10% | 0% |
| Team FTEs | -20% | +150% | +20% |

Note: Gross Revenue is derived from AGI if not adjusted — it moves proportionally unless manually overridden. This follows the same implied variable logic as the Calculator.

