### 2.3 Block 3 — Run & Save Actions

**Purpose:** Execute the scenario calculation and save the result.

#### Default State (Before Run)

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                                                     │
│         [ ↗ Run Scenario Analysis ]                 │
│                                                     │
│  Calculation runs instantly. Results saved to       │
│  your scenario library.                             │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

- Primary button: full-width or prominently centered, dark fill, white text
- Supporting micro-copy below button: light, small, sets expectation
- No reset button needed here — adjusting sliders is already non-destructive

#### Running State (During Calculation)

Button transitions to loading state — spinner replaces arrow icon, label changes to "Running Analysis…"

Duration: calculation is near-instant client-side. Loading state exists only to confirm the action was registered. 300–500ms minimum display even if calculation is faster.

#### Post-Run State (Save Prompt — Inline Expansion)

Immediately after run completes, the block expands inline below the button. No modal, no page change.

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  ✓  Scenario calculated                             │
│                                                     │
│  GVI Score: 67  ·  Healthy Velocity                 │
│  Ambition-Driven                                    │
│                                                     │
│  Give this scenario a name to save it:              │
│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────┐    │
│  │  Active Growth — 24mo                       │    │
│  └─────────────────────────────────────────────┘    │
│                                                     │
│  [ Save Scenario ]          [ Discard ]             │
│                                                     │
│  Saving adds this to your comparison library.       │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

- Checkmark + "Scenario calculated" confirmation — green, small
- GVI Score and band name displayed prominently — gives the founder immediate signal before saving
- Composition label on second line — lighter weight
- Name field: pre-populated with a suggested name based on dominant metric change and timeframe
  - Suggested name logic: "[Preset name] — [Timeframe]" if preset used, or "[Primary metric] +[%] — [Timeframe]" if custom
  - Examples: "Active Growth — 24mo", "AGI +75% — 18mo", "Conservative Climb — 36mo"
- Save button: primary, full-width within the block
- Discard: text link, right-aligned or secondary placement — low visual weight

#### Post-Save State (Confirmation)

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  ✓  "Active Growth — 24mo" saved                   │
│                                                     │
│  This scenario is now available in your             │
│  comparison view.                                   │
│                                                     │
│  [ View in Comparison ]    [ Build Another ]        │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

- "View in Comparison" — navigates to comparison section (scrolls down or switches sub-tab)
- "Build Another" — resets Block 2 sliders to default positions, clears the save prompt, ready for next scenario
- Baseline Block 1 is NOT reset — the starting point stays the same

