## Section 3 — Interaction States & Behavior

### 3.1 Slider Interaction

| State | Visual Behavior |
|---|---|
| Default | Track visible, thumb at position matching current value |
| Hover | Thumb slightly enlarges, cursor changes to grab |
| Active/Dragging | Thumb enlarges, percentage badge and value display update in real time |
| At baseline (0%) | Baseline tick mark aligns with thumb, percentage badge shows "0%" in neutral color |
| Positive adjustment | Left track fills with green-tinted accent |
| Negative adjustment | Left track fills with amber-tinted color |

### 3.2 Value Field Click-to-Edit

| State | Visual Behavior |
|---|---|
| Default | Value displayed as formatted text, pencil icon appears on hover |
| Clicked | Transitions to input field, value selected for replacement |
| Editing | Clear input field with cursor, slider grayed out (temporarily inactive) |
| On Enter/Blur | Value validates, slider repositions to match, percentage badge updates, field returns to display mode |
| Invalid entry | Field border turns red, value reverts to last valid on blur |

### 3.3 Baseline Source Indicator States

| State | Indicator |
|---|---|
| Snapshot data loaded, unedited | 🟢 "Using Agency Snapshot data" |
| Any field manually edited | 🟡 "Custom baseline — [n] fields modified" |
| Sync button clicked | Brief loading state, then returns to 🟢 state, all fields reset |

### 3.4 Preset Chip States

| State | Visual |
|---|---|
| Default | Outlined, light background |
| Hover | Border darkens, slight background tint |
| Selected | Filled background (accent), white text, ✓ prefix |
| Deselected by customization | Returns to default — no chip shown as selected |

### 3.5 Empty / First Load State

When the Scenario Planner tab is opened for the first time or if Agency Snapshot has no data:

- Block 1 fields show empty with placeholder values in muted text
- A banner above Block 1: "Complete your Agency Snapshot to auto-populate your baseline" with a link to the Snapshot tool
- Sliders and presets are still usable — founder can manually enter baseline values
- Run Scenario button is disabled until all required baseline fields have values

Required baseline fields: Annual AGI, Client Count, Retention Rate, Profit Margin, Team FTEs.

