## Section 4 — Run & Save Flow (Technical Behavior)

### 4.1 On "Run Scenario Analysis" Click

1. Resolve all input variables through the Explicit → Implied → Proxy hierarchy (same logic as Calculator — reference `lib/gviCalculations.ts`)
2. Run `calculateGVIScore()` with resolved variables
3. Build `inputs` payload (raw + resolved) matching Section 2.1 of `GVS_Supabase_Migration_Spec.md`
4. Build `results` payload matching Section 2.2 of `GVS_Supabase_Migration_Spec.md`
5. Build `implications` payload (template-driven) matching Section 2.3
6. Write record to `gvs_growth_scenarios` with `status = 'pending'`
7. Trigger n8n webhook with new record `id`
8. Surface post-run UI state with GVI score, band, and composition label
9. Hold runtime record `id` in local state for use in save action

### 4.2 On "Save Scenario" Click

1. Take the scenario name from the name field
2. Copy full runtime record payload into `gvs_saved_growth_scenarios`:
   - `scenario_name` from name field
   - `inputs`, `results`, `implications`, `gvi_score` from runtime record
   - `runtime_scenario_id` = runtime record `id`
   - `synthesis_content` = null at save time (GPT may not have returned yet)
3. Flip `is_saved = true` and `saved_at = now()` on runtime record
4. Surface post-save confirmation state
5. Scenario is now available in comparison section

### 4.3 Realtime Synthesis Update

The Realtime subscription established in the wiring pass continues to apply here. When n8n returns `synthesis_content` and flips `status = 'complete'` on the runtime record, if the scenario has already been saved, also update `synthesis_content` on the `gvs_saved_growth_scenarios` record. The founder may have already navigated to the comparison section — the synthesis content should populate there when it arrives.

### 4.4 "Build Another" Reset Behavior

Resets:
- All Block 2 slider positions to default (0% or preset defaults)
- Preset chip selection (none selected)
- Timeframe back to 24 Months
- Post-run and post-save prompt dismissed

Does NOT reset:
- Block 1 baseline fields
- Baseline source indicator

